  "elapsed_s": 7.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, there almost, almost a hundred people.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They were the leaders of the community and their wives.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And it was a very major event.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And my presentation or my [NON-ENGLISH] was taken from a topic which was introduced by my great-grandfather after whom I am named, [NON-ENGLISH] Yitzchak, or in Jewish, [NON-ENGLISH] Shmelkes, who was the Orthodox rabbi of Lwow at the turn of the century.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My father had some friends at the university because he was interested in Greek and Latin literature and classics.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So he had some friends.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Also, he had many contacts there with the non-Jewish community.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He was very highly regarded.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But it was not common to have too many relations with non-Jews.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The only contact which he had was with Archbishop Andrew Graf Szeptycki [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] because of circumstances which existed in Lwow, namely, there was a very prominent man who celebrated his 70th birthday.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And when my father read that the Roman Catholic clergy ignored it, although he was a Roman Catholic archbishop-- Greek Catholic archbishop, not Roman Catholic.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So my father headed a delegation to greet the man in the name of the Jewish community because he was very friendly, very correct, toward the Jewish community and usually also made contributions to charitable causes.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There's evidence of it.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "In your home-- we're talking about your bar mitzvah in 1938.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, yes, no question about it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That's a very complicated question because, you see, people didn't have the knowledge which they have today.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Secondly, they didn't fully comprehend the depth of the hatred which was cultivated by the leaders of the Third Reich-- and the danger.",
      "word_count": 23
    }
  ],
